description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you an enthusiastic, motivated and caring professional looking for a new challenge and new way of working? Are you looking to work in a team which is strongly committed to professional development and offering continuous in-house training opportunities?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;If so, come and join us!&lt;/em&gt;  Our friendly and multi-disciplinary team is excited to welcome more staff to join the ‘family’.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you a friendly, welcoming and supportive work environment and help you to develop your knowledge and skills!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;** We are currently offering £2,500 Golden Hello Payment to external candidates! **&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High recommendations have been received for this team:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;“Real team-working, friendly and feels supported, like a family”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;“I’ve had training opportunities to support my professional development’’&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;“This is a supportive team, committed to delivering high quality care”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;‘’good line management and I have regular monthly supervision”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span&gt;We are looking for skilled and dedicated individuals to join our expanding North and Mid team based in Basingstoke. As a member of the team, you will support the delivery of responsive, evidence based recovery focused care to the service users in acute mental health crisis. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You need be highly motivated, confident, and have the relevant experience, skills and knowledge for this role. You will also need to have previous experience in effective and positive management of people with mental health needs, and have a passion for working with mental health illness individuals and their families to deliver high quality of care and support throughout their recovery process. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent clinical skills and be able to demonstrate an ability to complete comprehensive mental state examinations, thoroughly assess risk, formulate safe and effective risk management plans and document this clearly and concisely is also essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;It is desirable that applicants are flexible and able to work shifts and unsociable hours as required. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;  &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Southern Health Foundation Trust will also offer you the below benefits: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           £1,000 if you recommend a friend to come and work in the trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Relocation package up to £8,000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Cycle to work scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Generous annual leave entitlement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Regular clinical supervision and training opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Free parking on site&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           A range of staff discounts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Childcare vouchers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ability to drive and use of a car for work purpose is essential in this role!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For informal discussions please contact Kate Lloyd 01256 376413 or by email katrina.lloyd@southernhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
